of granting
a temporary restraining order.

11:05.198 --> 11:10.370 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's a high hurdle for a
lawyer to meet
in a courtroom to get a judge to
grant a TRO,

11:10.403 --> 11:12.238 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a temporary restraining order.

11:12.272 --> 11:15.575 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, given that and the fact the
Ninth Circuit
declined to give an emergency
stay a couple

11:15.608 --> 11:19.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
nights ago, we feel confident
with our case
not just at the Ninth Circuit,
but frankly

11:19.812 --> 11:22.448 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
all the way up to the U.S.
Supreme Court,
if that's what it comes down to.

11:22.482 --> 11:25.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And all this is right
now is just
over this temporary restraining
order.

11:25.852 --> 11:30.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You would still have to go back
for a trial
on the merits before Judge
Robart in Seattle,

11:30.990 --> 11:32.659 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is that right?

11:32.692 --> 11:35.261 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BOB FERGUSON: That's correct,
although we
feel confident there, because in
order to

11:35.295 --> 11:41.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
grant the temporary restraining
order, one
of the criteria that the judge
must conclude

11:41.234 --> 11:45.071 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
