travel.

17:22.074 --> 17:23.042 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How do you respond to that?

17:23.075 --> 17:24.877 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

17:24.911 --> 17:26.612 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TED YOHO: You know, I think
those are talking
points that people are throwing
out there.

17:26.646 --> 17:28.114 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There is going to be some
inconvenience.

17:28.147 --> 17:30.416 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But how inconvenient was 9/11?

17:30.449 --> 17:34.353 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How inconvenient were the
attacks in Belgium
and Brussels?

17:34.387 --> 17:40.326 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those were extreme consequences
that came
from not vetting people
properly.

17:40.359 --> 17:42.128 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We don't want to make that
mistake.

17:42.161 --> 17:45.364 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Would you rather make the
mistake and err
on the side of caution or wait
until something

17:45.398 --> 17:49.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
happens and then answer to the
American people,
why you didn't vet these people
properly?

17:50.002 --> 17:53.839 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: In the last Congress,
you were
on the House Foreign Affairs
Subcommittee

17:53.873 --> 17:55.641 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on Terrorism.

17:55.675 --> 17:58.844 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Are these countries, the
countries that are
specified in the executive
order, given your

17:58.878 --> 18:01.914 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
experience on that panel, are
these the countries
you would have chosen?

18:01.948 --> 18:03.149 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

18:03.182 --> 18:05.384 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TED YOHO: I think these are good
countries
to put on there.

18:05.418 --> 18:08.354 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You look at Syria, you look at
Somalia, you
look at these other ones, they
don't have

18:08.387 --> 18:13.359 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the infrastructure or the I.T.
to go back
and look at somebody's birth
record, their

18:13.392 --> 18:15.561 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
